<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="256" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1794,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" box="[199,400,1831,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1986) [Species of the genus Aprionus (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) in forested lowland and forest-steppe zones of the Ukraine.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1986 (5), 75 - 79." type="journal article" year="1986">
Berest (
<number box="[288,349,1831,1856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="1986.0">1986</number>
: 
<number box="[363,392,1831,1855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="77.0">77</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
distinguished 
<taxonomicName box="[569,685,1831,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis box="[569,685,1831,1855]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">A. lobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species she regarded as closely related to but distinct from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">A. acutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with reference to the “obliquely truncated edge of the apical gonocoxal lobe”. Her meaning is understandable from the genital illustration of the 
<typeStatus box="[710,808,1903,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">holotype</typeStatus>
male (
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" box="[883,1091,1903,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1986) [Species of the genus Aprionus (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) in forested lowland and forest-steppe zones of the Ukraine.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1986 (5), 75 - 79." type="journal article" year="1986">
Berest 
<number box="[963,1023,1903,1928]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="1986.0">1986</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[1078,1091,1903,1927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="1.0">1</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the only specimen the author had available. The figure shows that the lobe-like extensions at the apices of the gonocoxites are not symmetrically shaped: one lobe is subtriangular, resembling the shape in 
<taxonomicName box="[799,902,1975,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Cecidomyiidae" genus="Aprionus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="acutus">
<emphasis box="[799,902,1975,1999]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="256">A. acutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Jaschhof" box="[916,1194,1975,2000]" pageId="1" pageNumber="262" refString="Jaschhof, M. (1998) Revision der &quot; Lestremiinae &quot; (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) der Holarktis. Studia dipterologica Supplement, 4, 1 - 552." type="journal article" year="1998" yearSuffix="a">
Jaschhof 
<number box="[1022,1082,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="1998.0">1998</number>
: fig. 
<number box="[1137,1181,1975,1999]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="133.0">133</number>
a
</bibRefCitation>
), while the other lobe is blunt-ended, due to distortion. 
<bibRefCitation author="Berest" box="[522,675,2011,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="261" refString="Berest, Z. L. (1986) [Species of the genus Aprionus (Diptera, Cecidomyiidae) in forested lowland and forest-steppe zones of the Ukraine.] Vestnik Zoologii, 1986 (5), 75 - 79." type="journal article" year="1986">
Berest (
<number box="[608,666,2011,2036]" pageId="1" pageNumber="256" value="1986.0">1986</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
described the distorted rather than the undistorted lobe.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
